{"word":"G2727 - κατηχέω - katēchéō - kat-ay-kheh'-o - Inform","slug":"G2727","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">κατηχέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>katēchéō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kat-ay-kheh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Inform"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x03C4;&#x03B7;&#x03C7;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - kate&#x0304;cheo&#x0304;</b> - <i>kat-ay-kheh'-o</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G2596\">G2596</a> and <a href=\"#/G2279\">G2279</a>; to <i>sound down</i> into the ears, that is, (by implication) to <i>indoctrinate</i> (&ldquo;catechize&rdquo;) or (generally) to <i>apprise</i> of: - inform, instruct, teach."}]}